982
01:13:24,206 --> 01:13:26,037
I'm allergic to chickens.

983
01:13:31,766 --> 01:13:34,917
Wait. What about the other night?

984
01:13:35,726 --> 01:13:38,877
We were like two stars
in the same constellation.

985
01:13:40,286 --> 01:13:44,962
Michael, you and I are light-years apart.
You should go, but not with me.

986
01:13:45,046 --> 01:13:49,756
But we had heat, baby. Passion! Fire!

987
01:13:50,686 --> 01:13:53,802
We owe it to ourselves to fuse together.

988
01:13:54,846 --> 01:13:56,757
At least one more time.

989
01:13:57,686 --> 01:14:00,996
That's a great line.
You are going to be a terrific writer.

990
01:14:03,006 --> 01:14:05,679
- You think so?
- Yeah.

991
01:14:06,686 --> 01:14:11,680
Michael,
we had one glorious night together.

992
01:14:12,365 --> 01:14:15,199
Someday you'll remember
and write about it.

993
01:14:17,405 --> 01:14:18,521
Yeah.

994
01:14:20,126 --> 01:14:21,114
I can dig that.

995
01:14:23,246 --> 01:14:25,157
Bittersweet perfection.

996
01:14:25,926 --> 01:14:30,158
Dogs of lust on leashes of memory. Yes!

997
01:14:33,166 --> 01:14:34,599
It's Charlie.

998
01:14:35,046 --> 01:14:36,479
What a treat.

999
01:14:39,926 --> 01:14:41,074
Now I get it.

1000
01:14:41,686 --> 01:14:43,085
It's great.

1001
01:14:44,445 --> 01:14:47,643
Peggy Sue's still stuck on
"Treble Without a Cause."

1002
01:14:48,206 --> 01:14:50,117
Come on, I want to dance.

1003
01:15:10,046 --> 01:15:12,560
I thought I knew everything about him.

1004
01:15:12,886 --> 01:15:14,399
Can we split now?

1005
01:15:42,605 --> 01:15:43,925
Thank you.

1006
01:15:46,886 --> 01:15:49,081
So, Mr. Wilkins, new client?

1007
01:15:50,286 --> 01:15:51,958
I'm sorry, Charlie.

1008
01:15:55,445 --> 01:15:57,516
I don't think so, you know.

1009
01:15:58,846 --> 01:16:01,041
It happens, but not with you.

1010
01:16:01,326 --> 01:16:02,884
Believe me when I tell you.

1011
01:16:02,966 --> 01:16:05,525
Maybe it's the material.
But it can't happen.

1012
01:16:29,166 --> 01:16:30,394
Good morning.

1013
01:16:33,405 --> 01:16:34,838
Charlie?

1014
01:16:43,926 --> 01:16:45,882
What are you doing here?

1015
01:16:46,326 --> 01:16:48,282
I wanted to talk to you.

1016
01:16:48,726 --> 01:16:52,162
I've got one last thing
I have to do at school and then...

1017
01:16:53,286 --> 01:16:56,561
Elvis. Hi. How are you? Hi, guy.

1018
01:16:56,646 --> 01:16:58,716
Elvis is dead. That's Ajax.

1019
01:17:01,485 --> 01:17:03,636
I guess I always liked Elvis.

1020
01:17:04,485 --> 01:17:06,875
- Can I have a ride to school?
- No.

1021
01:17:07,246 --> 01:17:10,761
- Why?
- The tiger's out of commission for a while.

1022
01:17:11,006 --> 01:17:12,041
Come on.

1023
01:17:12,286 --> 01:17:16,324
- How about a walk, Charlie Bell?
- How did you know about that?

1024
01:17:16,485 --> 01:17:18,875
I was at Lena's last night.
I heard you sing.

1025
01:17:18,966 --> 01:17:20,604
I thought you were terrific.

1026
01:17:20,686 --> 01:17:23,279
Not terrific enough.
What were you doing there?

1027
01:17:23,365 --> 01:17:26,085
- Who were you with?
- Well, what were you doing there?

1028
01:17:26,166 --> 01:17:28,360
You never told me you sang
with an R & B group.

1029
01:17:28,445 --> 01:17:32,324
There's not a whole heck of a lot
we know about each other, Peggy.

1030
01:17:33,646 --> 01:17:37,878
- I forgot how much music meant to you.
- That's real big of you.

1031
01:17:38,326 --> 01:17:40,556
Stop being so defensive. Here.

1032
01:17:41,686 --> 01:17:43,596
I wrote a song for you.

1033
01:17:45,286 --> 01:17:48,914
- Why did you write me a song?
- Because I want to help you.

1034
01:17:50,445 --> 01:17:54,279
- It'll be a hit. I promise.
- Come on! Stop being sarcastic.

1035
01:17:54,886 --> 01:17:57,559
Lee Wilkins came to hear me last night.

1036
01:17:57,806 --> 01:18:00,400
He told me to forget it.

1037
01:18:02,365 --> 01:18:04,436
Would you just take a look at it?

1038
01:18:04,886 --> 01:18:07,036
Come on. I wrote it for you.

1039
01:18:08,006 --> 01:18:11,282
Well, if you wrote it I guess I'll look at it.

1040
01:18:13,886 --> 01:18:17,355
Listen, about the other night,
I feel so stupid.

1041
01:18:18,445 --> 01:18:22,837
I'm beginning to think that maybe
there is more to life than just music.

1042
01:18:24,686 --> 01:18:29,077
Do you think the world would still like me
if I stopped being Mr. Excitement?

1043
01:18:32,046 --> 01:18:33,161
Yeah.

1044
01:18:35,206 --> 01:18:37,400
Do you want to walk to school?

1045
01:18:38,046 --> 01:18:40,195
Okay, I'll just put the dog inside.

1046
01:18:40,846 --> 01:18:42,119
Come on, Ajax.

1047
01:18:45,846 --> 01:18:48,644
What's the matter, princess?
Lost your prince?

1048
01:18:49,966 --> 01:18:53,675
Delores, there are a lot of things
I could say to you...

1049
01:18:53,846 --> 01:18:56,235
...but you're just not worth the effort.

1050
01:18:57,525 --> 01:19:02,122
- I'm so sorry. These pens are so tricky, I...
- You did that on purpose!

1051
01:19:02,766 --> 01:19:06,315
I hate you! Go stuff your bra!

1052
01:19:07,046 --> 01:19:10,721
- I beg your pardon?
- Take a long walk on a short pier.

1053
01:19:11,166 --> 01:19:12,757
Have a nice day.

1054
01:19:25,886 --> 01:19:29,925
You know, Peggy, there are so many things
to look forward to in the future.

1055
01:19:34,086 --> 01:19:35,997
I came to say good-bye, Richard.

1056
01:19:36,086 --> 01:19:39,283
Good-bye? Wait a minute. Sit down.

1057
01:19:40,846 --> 01:19:45,283
Good-bye? Where are you going?
Peggy, we have a partnership here.

1058
01:19:45,365 --> 01:19:48,914
- I'm making progress on that microchip.
- Well, you were meant to.

1059
01:19:49,006 --> 01:19:51,520
You're one of the people
good things happen to.

1060
01:19:51,605 --> 01:19:52,754
So are you.

1061
01:19:53,086 --> 01:19:55,963
- You have a vision, Peggy.
- A vision?

1062
01:19:57,006 --> 01:19:59,075
I am a walking anachronism!

1063
01:20:00,086 --> 01:20:03,316
I've upset my parents. I miss my kids.

1064
01:20:03,605 --> 01:20:07,360
I could be trapped here forever.
And poor Charlie.

1065
01:20:07,525 --> 01:20:11,360
I got pregnant when I was 18.
That was why we had to get married.

1066
01:20:11,806 --> 01:20:13,319
Tomorrow's my birthday.

1067
01:20:13,405 --> 01:20:16,921
- I have to get out of here.
- You broke up with Charlie?

1068
01:20:18,006 --> 01:20:20,395
Yeah. I know it's a gamble.

1069
01:20:21,125 --> 01:20:23,480
I've loved him for a long, long time.

1070
01:20:23,605 --> 01:20:26,722
Okay. Then let's do something
really visionary.

1071
01:20:27,006 --> 01:20:29,280
Change your destiny, Peggy Sue.

1072
01:20:29,926 --> 01:20:33,281
Change your destiny and marry me.

1073
01:20:34,926 --> 01:20:39,396
No! Peggy Sue got married.

1074
01:20:39,926 --> 01:20:41,324
Case closed.

1075
01:20:42,046 --> 01:20:44,640
I don't want to marry anyone, Richard.

1076
01:20:45,165 --> 01:20:46,154
Good-bye.

1077
01:20:46,445 --> 01:20:48,834
Wait! Peggy, please. Can I go with you?

1078
01:20:48,926 --> 01:20:52,077
No! You have to be valedictorian.

1079
01:20:59,006 --> 01:21:00,997
Peggy Sue, wait a minute!

1080
01:21:01,445 --> 01:21:04,756
Listen, I cut shop
and I did some work on your song.

1081
01:21:05,686 --> 01:21:08,119
You know, it's not half bad
for your first try.

1082
01:21:08,205 --> 01:21:11,278
I changed all the "yeahs" to "oohs,"
but listen to this:

1083
01:21:11,365 --> 01:21:14,756
"She loves you, ooh, ooh, ooh
You love me, ooh, ooh, ooh"

1084
01:21:16,405 --> 01:21:17,555
I got to go.

1085
01:21:17,646 --> 01:21:21,160
About your birthday.
I made reservations at Chez Trev.

1086
01:21:21,525 --> 01:21:24,404
I thought it would be great to eat
at a nice restaurant.

1087
01:21:24,485 --> 01:21:26,078
I won't be here.

1088
01:21:26,565 --> 01:21:29,717
- Why?
- I want to go see my grandparents.

1089
01:21:30,766 --> 01:21:32,404
Good-bye, Charlie.

1090
01:21:33,285 --> 01:21:35,753
I cancelled the tickets for Fabian.

1091
01:22:22,046 --> 01:22:23,114
Close that.

1092
01:22:23,205 --> 01:22:24,923
- There you are.
- Thank you.

1093
01:22:26,846 --> 01:22:30,475
Look! Oh, it's so beautiful.

1094
01:23:03,966 --> 01:23:07,321
What's the matter, Peggy?
Someone jump on your grave?

1095
01:23:14,605 --> 01:23:18,440
You know, Peggy, your mother said
you had a dream that I died.

1096
01:23:19,245 --> 01:23:21,077
I wish she hadn't have told you that.

1097
01:23:21,165 --> 01:23:24,954
I'm not afraid.
I know exactly when I'm going to die.

1098
01:23:25,046 --> 01:23:28,561
What's it going to be, Lizzy?
Seventy-five or eighty?

1099
01:23:29,565 --> 01:23:31,158
I'm not telling!

1100
01:23:31,245 --> 01:23:34,123
I've been trying to drag
that out of her for years.

1101
01:23:34,285 --> 01:23:37,083
You know,
dreams are a fascinating business.

1102
01:23:37,205 --> 01:23:41,199
- Especially when you see the future.
- Do you believe all this?

1103
01:23:41,525 --> 01:23:45,598
Well, I like to speculate.
Like this book I'm reading right now.

1104
01:23:45,686 --> 01:23:50,680
It's about a woman in Colorado who says
she lived in Ireland 150 years ago.

1105
01:23:51,365 --> 01:23:54,199
She gives names,
dates and where she lived.

1106
01:23:55,525 --> 01:23:57,163
Grandma. Grandpa.

1107
01:23:59,165 --> 01:24:01,235
I want to tell you something.

1108
01:24:05,686 --> 01:24:09,395
If you believe it, darling, then I believe.

1109
01:24:10,405 --> 01:24:13,397
Being young is just as confusing
as being old.

1110
01:24:14,565 --> 01:24:17,079
The things that happened to me
50 years ago...

1111
01:24:17,165 --> 01:24:20,316
...are more on my mind
than the things that happen today.

1112
01:24:21,285 --> 01:24:23,561
But I'm remembering the future.

1113
01:24:25,325 --> 01:24:27,281
A chilling wind tonight.

1114
01:24:28,886 --> 01:24:30,524
It's really picking up.

1115
01:24:30,605 --> 01:24:34,154
Right now,
you're just browsing through time.

1116
01:24:36,165 --> 01:24:38,759
Choose the things you'll be proud of.

1117
01:24:39,205 --> 01:24:40,843
Things that last.

1118
01:24:41,886 --> 01:24:43,877
I'm proud of my children.

1119
01:24:44,285 --> 01:24:46,038
I miss them so much.

1120
01:24:46,485 --> 01:24:49,159
Scott and Beth.

1121
01:24:50,646 --> 01:24:52,556
I named my daughter after you.

1122
01:24:55,086 --> 01:24:58,476
Sweetheart, thank you.

1123
01:25:04,766 --> 01:25:05,994
Grandpa.

1124
01:25:09,006 --> 01:25:11,883
When you and Grandma are gone,
the family's gone.

1125
01:25:11,966 --> 01:25:13,957
And I'll never see the cousins anymore.

1126
01:25:14,046 --> 01:25:17,833
It's your grandma's strudel
that's kept this family together.

1127
01:25:18,125 --> 01:25:22,244
If you could do it all again, Grandpa,
what would you do different?

1128
01:25:22,846 --> 01:25:25,519
I'd have taken better care of my teeth.

1129
01:25:26,245 --> 01:25:29,283
Now what's Peggy Sue going to do
at your lodge meeting?

1130
01:25:30,525 --> 01:25:33,437
It's her 18th birthday
and I want to show her off.

1131
01:25:33,605 --> 01:25:37,154
It was my idea, Grandma.
I wondered about those lodge meetings.

1132
01:25:37,245 --> 01:25:39,601
He won't tell me.
But I have my suspicions.

1133
01:25:39,686 --> 01:25:41,915
I don't want to know.
Have a good time, darling.

1134
01:25:42,006 --> 01:25:43,324
All right.

1135
01:25:45,205 --> 01:25:47,515
- Good-bye.
- Good-bye, darling.

1136
01:25:48,966 --> 01:25:50,194
Grandpa?

1137
01:25:50,525 --> 01:25:53,244
What does Grandma think you do
at these meetings?

1138
01:25:53,325 --> 01:25:55,156
Stag movies and poker.

1139
01:26:01,405 --> 01:26:04,875
I may be an old fool,
but I think I can help you.

1140
01:26:06,445 --> 01:26:09,324
At least I got to see you
and Grandma again.

1141
01:26:10,205 --> 01:26:12,355
Has this ever worked before?

1142
01:26:12,485 --> 01:26:17,275
The last time was 600 years ago.
And it's about time for another one.

1143
01:26:44,165 --> 01:26:46,281
Welcome, Peggy Sue!

1144
01:26:46,766 --> 01:26:49,837
Peggy Sue! Welcome, Peggy Sue!

1145
01:26:49,966 --> 01:26:52,843
- It's so wonderful to have you here with us.
- Thank you.

1146
01:26:52,926 --> 01:26:56,521
You've come to the right place.
Our lodge was founded by a time traveller.

1147
01:26:56,605 --> 01:26:59,039
- We're going to send you back home.
- That's right!

1148
01:26:59,125 --> 01:27:01,320
You know, this is very exciting for all of us.

1149
01:27:01,405 --> 01:27:05,637
You know, we've waited a long time
to find a girl like you.

1150
01:27:05,766 --> 01:27:06,834
Yes!

1151
01:27:06,926 --> 01:27:10,838
Grandpa! Do you have to wear that hat?

1152
01:27:11,205 --> 01:27:12,843
Wouldn't be a lodge without hats.

1153
01:28:07,325 --> 01:28:09,123
"Lord of the universe.

1154
01:28:10,165 --> 01:28:11,918
"Vast and mighty one.

1155
01:28:12,686 --> 01:28:14,199
"Ruler of light.

1156
01:28:15,245 --> 01:28:16,837
"King of the sun.

1157
01:28:17,125 --> 01:28:20,038
"This girl is lost amid your mysteries...

1158
01:28:20,125 --> 01:28:22,765
"...and wishes to return to her own time.

1159
01:28:23,205 --> 01:28:26,198
"We adore thee and invoke thee!

1160
01:28:26,605 --> 01:28:28,198
"Grant thine aid.

1161
01:28:28,726 --> 01:28:33,516
"Look with favour upon us
as we witness the regeneration of spirit.

1162
01:28:35,285 --> 01:28:37,038
"We ask thy intervention...

1163
01:28:37,125 --> 01:28:42,074
"...that this girl may return to thee
on the wings of thy love."

1164
01:28:43,926 --> 01:28:48,204
"Womb of the mother,
reclaim thy child of light."

1165
01:28:48,766 --> 01:28:51,154
"The name of your love is rebirth."

1166
01:28:51,605 --> 01:28:54,484
- This is never going to work.
- It's going to work!

1167
01:28:54,565 --> 01:28:57,364
"Reclaim thy child of light."

1168
01:28:57,445 --> 01:29:02,440
"We offer up this girl
that her soul may find its home."

1169
01:29:10,766 --> 01:29:15,521
It's nothing to worry about.
Somebody get the lights.

1170
01:29:17,245 --> 01:29:19,601
Somebody get the lights!

1171
01:29:22,525 --> 01:29:23,561
She's gone!

1172
01:29:25,846 --> 01:29:28,279
What the hell do you think you're doing?

1173
01:29:28,726 --> 01:29:31,717
I'm saving you!
They were going to vaporise you!

1174
01:29:31,806 --> 01:29:36,163
Don't be ridiculous! They're harmless
old men! My grandfather was in there!

1175
01:29:36,245 --> 01:29:38,713
- Get in the car!
- I'm not getting in this monstrosity!

1176
01:29:39,006 --> 01:29:40,837
Well, the girl's gone.

1177
01:29:41,125 --> 01:29:42,763
Let's play cards.

1178
01:29:54,886 --> 01:29:58,400
I've got good news.
Now sit down right here.

1179
01:29:58,726 --> 01:30:00,239
You've got two minutes!

1180
01:30:00,325 --> 01:30:03,159
I told my father
that I'm going to quit singing.

1181
01:30:03,245 --> 01:30:07,034
And he gave me 10 percent
of the business right now!

1182
01:30:07,125 --> 01:30:10,641
- What are you talking about?
- I know what you've been going through.

1183
01:30:10,726 --> 01:30:12,762
You were just scared.

1184
01:30:12,926 --> 01:30:16,601
But you don't have to be scared anymore.
I can support you now.

1185
01:30:16,686 --> 01:30:18,836
- Shit!
- Peggy Sue?

1186
01:30:20,086 --> 01:30:21,803
Will you marry me?

1187
01:30:21,886 --> 01:30:24,115
How can you know
what I've been going through?

1188
01:30:24,205 --> 01:30:27,516
Of course I'm scared!
I can't change anything.

1189
01:30:27,605 --> 01:30:29,961
- I can't help anybody.
- You're not listening to me.

1190
01:30:30,046 --> 01:30:32,400
- I'm proposing to you now.
- You betrayed me.

1191
01:30:32,485 --> 01:30:34,681
You were never there for me
and the children.

1192
01:30:34,766 --> 01:30:38,678
I'll be there for the children.
I'll forget Walter.

1193
01:30:39,125 --> 01:30:42,641
Forget the group. I want to marry you!

1194
01:30:42,886 --> 01:30:44,034
Don't be crazy.

1195
01:30:44,125 --> 01:30:47,879
I may be crazy, but I'm not crazy enough
to marry you twice.

1196
01:30:49,726 --> 01:30:50,999
Christ.

1197
01:30:52,726 --> 01:30:53,954
Peggy.

1198
01:30:57,205 --> 01:30:58,605
I'm sorry.

1199
01:31:02,525 --> 01:31:06,074
I thought I was what you wanted me to be.

1200
01:31:07,565 --> 01:31:09,238
It's all my fault.

1201
01:31:14,565 --> 01:31:15,681
Here.

1202
01:31:17,086 --> 01:31:19,042
It's a birthday present.

1203
01:31:20,525 --> 01:31:23,279
I'm tired of being the romantic fool.

1204
01:31:24,686 --> 01:31:26,802
I'm going to go save my car.

1205
01:31:28,285 --> 01:31:29,513
Charlie?

1206
01:31:32,846 --> 01:31:34,324
It opens, too.

1207
01:31:34,806 --> 01:31:36,204
Look inside.

1208
01:31:42,086 --> 01:31:45,396
Scott and Beth. Where did you get this?

1209
01:31:45,926 --> 01:31:47,837
Who are Scott and Beth?

1210
01:31:49,006 --> 01:31:51,360
Your mother gave me those.
It's you and me.

1211
01:31:51,445 --> 01:31:52,924
You know that.

1212
01:31:54,926 --> 01:31:58,680
So are they.

1213
01:31:59,966 --> 01:32:01,637
I do love you.

1214
01:32:02,285 --> 01:32:03,638
I love you.

1215
01:32:06,766 --> 01:32:08,757
This is right, Peggy Sue.

1216
01:32:10,766 --> 01:32:12,802
I want this to be forever.

1217
01:32:20,766 --> 01:32:22,517
Mom, can you hear me?

1218
01:32:24,806 --> 01:32:26,682
Please, Mom, can you hear me?

1219
01:32:26,766 --> 01:32:28,642
They call what happened a near-death...

1220
01:32:28,726 --> 01:32:31,285
...but we figured out
exactly what the problem is...

1221
01:32:31,365 --> 01:32:33,356
You are a very lucky young lady!

1222
01:32:33,525 --> 01:32:36,597
What happened to you, Peggy Sue,
was a very rare problem...

1223
01:32:36,686 --> 01:32:38,437
...with the rhythm of your heart.

1224
01:32:38,525 --> 01:32:40,004
Mom, do you remember anything?

1225
01:32:40,086 --> 01:32:44,079
In fact, at the party,
they had to do CPR on you...

1226
01:32:45,165 --> 01:32:48,874
...before the paramedics arrived
to give your heart a shock and restart it.

1227
01:32:49,006 --> 01:32:51,042
Dad's been here every day.

1228
01:32:51,365 --> 01:32:53,641
"'Cause I love you, Peggy Sue

1229
01:32:58,565 --> 01:33:02,035
"I love you, girl, and I need you, Peggy"

1230
01:33:09,646 --> 01:33:10,998
Charlie?

1231
01:33:12,405 --> 01:33:16,319
- Was I dead?
- I thought you were for a while.

1232
01:33:18,525 --> 01:33:20,004
You look awful.

1233
01:33:20,525 --> 01:33:23,199
You look like you haven't slept in days.

1234
01:33:24,285 --> 01:33:27,323
- You look so old.
- But happy.

1235
01:33:28,565 --> 01:33:30,636
Very happy, Peggy.

1236
01:33:31,806 --> 01:33:35,082
I thought I knew everything about you.
I'm sorry.

1237
01:33:35,165 --> 01:33:37,202
I wanted to tell you that I...

1238
01:33:37,285 --> 01:33:39,401
- I wanted to...
- I'm sorry.

1239
01:33:39,525 --> 01:33:43,598
I can't live without you.

1240
01:33:46,605 --> 01:33:48,244
What about Janet?

1241
01:33:51,565 --> 01:33:55,400
That's over.
I got tired of translating everything to her.

1242
01:33:55,485 --> 01:33:58,319
She thought the Big Bopper
was a hamburger.

1243
01:34:03,046 --> 01:34:06,038
- Who are all the flowers from?
- Everyone.

1244
01:34:06,646 --> 01:34:10,320
Maddy and Arthur, Carol and Walter...

1245
01:34:11,445 --> 01:34:13,276
...Richard Norvik.

1246
01:34:14,365 --> 01:34:19,120
And here's a book by that guy
in high school, Michael Fitzsimmons.

1247
01:34:20,046 --> 01:34:21,957
He dedicated it to you.

1248
01:34:27,525 --> 01:34:29,801
It couldn't be me. I hardly knew him.

1249
01:34:33,686 --> 01:34:35,915
I'll just set this right here.

1250
01:34:40,485 --> 01:34:42,716
I had a strange experience.

1251
01:34:43,926 --> 01:34:47,759
I went back to high school
and I spent a lot of time with you.

1252
01:34:49,125 --> 01:34:53,482
You and Walter and Leon were singing
I Wonder Why.

1253
01:34:54,125 --> 01:34:55,638
God! Dion!

1254
01:34:56,285 --> 01:34:57,958
You were terrific.

1255
01:34:59,285 --> 01:35:02,083
And I kept trying to push you away.

1256
01:35:03,365 --> 01:35:06,482
- But you wouldn't give up.
- I'll never give up.

1257
01:35:08,285 --> 01:35:09,958
Would you hold me?

1258
01:35:14,245 --> 01:35:19,274
I don't expect that all our problems
can just vanish.

1259
01:35:21,966 --> 01:35:25,845
Christ, I would cut my right arm off
for another chance.

1260
01:35:25,926 --> 01:35:29,555
No, please, I need some time.

1261
01:35:41,766 --> 01:35:44,154
Well, I'll let you get some rest.

1262
01:35:54,405 --> 01:35:58,364
I'd like to invite you over to our house
for dinner on Sunday.

1263
01:35:59,086 --> 01:36:00,598
With your kids.

1264
01:36:04,125 --> 01:36:05,797
I'll make a strudel.

